OL,7,FThe jury previously heard how two boys
OL,8,Fwere asleep in cabin-style beds in one
OL,9,Fof the school's boarding houses when
OL,10,Fthe defendant climbed up and attacked
OL,11,Fthem shortly before 1am.
OL,13,FHe had armed himself with three claw
OL,14,Fhammers and waited for the two boys to
OL,15,Fbe asleep before launching the assault.
OL,17,FTheir housemaster, who was asleep in
OL,18,Fhis own quarters, was awoken by noises
OL,19,Fcoming from the boarding house and
OL,20,Fwent to investigate.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/21
