OL,7,FWhen he entered the bedroom, where the
OL,8,Fattack had happened, he saw a
OL,9,Fsilhouetted figure standing in the
OL,10,Froom who turned towards him and
OL,11,Frepeatedly struck him over the head
OL,12,Fwith a hammer.
OL,14,FIn interviews recorded by the police
OL,15,Fand played to the jury, one of the
OL,16,Fvictims told officers he and the
OL,17,Fdefendant had been friends in the
OL,18,Fprevious academic year but there was a
OL,19,F"complete change" after the summer
OL,20,Fholidays.
