OL,7,F"Their survival has nothing to do with
OL,8,Fthe defendant and his actions but
OL,9,Feverything to do with the speed at
OL,10,Fwhich the 999 call was made by a boy
OL,11,Fat school and the astonishing skill of
OL,12,Fthe paramedics who arrived and the
OL,13,Fskilful work of the doctors and
OL,14,Fsurgeons who saved their lives at the
OL,15,Fhospital."
OL,17,FMr Dawes said both boys are living
OL,18,Fwith the "long-term consequences" of
OL,19,Fthe attack but have no memory of the
OL,20,Fincident.
